import { useEffect, useState } from "react" import "./BookingForm.css" export const BookingForm = () => { const [genres, setGenres] = useState([]) useEffect( () => { fetch(`http://localhost:8088/genres`) .then(response => response()) .then((genreArray) => { setGenres(genreArray) }) }, [] ) return ( < div className="bookingForm" >
